[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test coverage setup**\n\nI need to think about the existing tests and whether the library requires more than just the usual test scaffold. The question is if we need additional setup like dependencies or system properties for meaningful coverage. \n\nIn the case of the vertx-web-client, it typically requires a network server, but in-process testing is possible without Docker. Extra dependencies, like OAuth2, are optional. However, proper coverage can be achieved without them. I need to clarify if specific runtime arguments are necessary for native Java 25 and if the same applies for version 5.0.1.\n\n**Investigating setup actions**\n\nI need to decide on actions regarding advisory preparations based on whether agent guidance includes runtime system properties. I should look into the issue stack, starting from entRequestImpl.writeQueueFull. It might not be necessarily tied to the `UnsupportedFeatureError` for sun.misc.Unsafe. \n\nCould it be a native run failure due to a test timing out? Running tests can be expensive, especially with library version 5.0.1. Currently, the build applies properties only for version 5.0.0. Maybe a javaTest run would be more efficient. I should also check the native build generated and see what system properties are needed for Java 25 related to Netty.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dfa6b2adfbe6ba9016a401ac31278819081562c86d7d81ed2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQBrLmV-q0HioucVVEs53tn1WUIvGPjgN7RD0vVDk09VwRSdBSSwjskUdy-pGFs2mAo2YETwwTrnL2lxnt5Y65vlXNRjAvGWGv-NrLd8S1ybPnik1nwwGxI5z9RvJwBdgXf3E32J0sLJSHUBgSj9xItaOFHGLpkUgqVz1OsfXgYU5GVYdi6IyZTIu2MmSknSFuGIvj5rgh9v_-ihzDv3fXQrqwzwEroRWjNVUqVuDg4lp-R8NbqROyr4rb6vWiIFybeAwcsYbIweNGR_48x_RsseuBEvdw4FDjVSHspPlA1iZ1-mWvALwTQOCryiPFX-bTDjudXc0gfO_OyAR0c8H8d-Xxy6wbr_oznGfsvlrmaAVVsqgJqaOtgVrMXLHVBy2rH2wWOVVWMzu5JwvYolenKb8VBxgRVzY6Q