   Github Wiki page?  You can improve it by yourself  here!                                           Java 24 integrated  JEP 498  and started printing warnings to the console, when  sun.misc.Unsafe  memory-access methods are first used.   Netty has historically been relying on these methods to more efficiently work with native (off-heap) memory. This means applications that use Netty, and run on Java 24 or greater, may see these warnings.     Netty 4.1 and U
  w">JEP 498  and started printing warnings to the console, when  sun.misc.Unsafe  memory-access methods are first used.   Netty has historically been relying on these methods to more efficiently work with native (off-heap) memory. This means applications that use Netty, and run on Java 24 or greater, may see these warnings.     Netty 4.1 and Unsafe    <path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 
